flowchart TD
    POP["`Population Everything we want to learn about (often impossible to fully measure)`"]
    POP --> SAMP["Sampling method Simple random / Stratified Cluster / Systematic"]
    SAMP --> SAM["`Sample Subset actually measured (n observations)`"]
    SAM --> STAT["Sample statistics x̄, s, p …"]
    STAT --> INFER["Statistical inference Estimate population parameters μ, σ, π …"]
    INFER -->|"Generalize — if sample is representative"| POP

    subgraph BIAS["Sampling bias risks"]
        B1["Non-random selection → sample not representative"]
        B2["Non-response bias → missing a systematic subgroup"]
        B3["Convenience sampling → easy to collect, hard to generalise"]
    end
    SAMP --> BIAS
